text: O clerice, ne dempseris umquam dipticas lateriEala ðu cleric ne wana ðu æfre wexbreda fram sidan.
Fugeas fore corcula labentis ludi, ne letetur te fedus sandapila neque toparchiaforfleoh wesan ealdor slidendes plegan þæt ne blissige fræte bær ne helle ealdor.
Sit machia tibi, quo sit ierarchia, neque sit cloaca tibigewin þæt sy halig ealdor ne ne sy helle pyt.
Non sit enteca nec alogia, uerum commoueat absida acrimonia mentes tecum, quia non mordetne sy feohgestreon ne oferfyl soðes gemingyge beorht strengð mod mid ðe forðam þe ne slit.

Fiat mens tui tuus agonitheta ambasilla, ne legat cromam praeter uranium, quia solet is esse deus multissy mod þin ðin winnend innoð ne geceose bleoh butan heofenlic forðam þe gewunað se wesan manegum.
Sectare gemellam anodiamfyli ðu getwinne læcedom.
Verere sistere sicophanta, adsis tamen boba, ne tangat griffia, charchesia togaque crebroondræd gewunian teonful stið þæt ne æthrine gewrita melas & reaf gelomlice.

Sistat frequens sintheca grammaton tibi; absistat uero glaucoma, offa criminis, longe, blataque brattea dehinc enclitica prosapia non absint ullatenus militie Christi per tegewunige gelomlic gesetednes stafena gewite dymnes snæd leahtres feor & brunbasu platung syððan eadmodlic mægð ne gewitan ateshwon cempan.
Existat amphitappa laon nec non badanola, diamant effipiam, stragulam pariterque propomamgewunige ruh hrægl læwedra eac swilce forbed þearle lufiað geræda brunbasu reaf gedrefedne drenc.
Est effipia, stragula, pretexta aulica curageræda brunbasu reaf & dyrwurðe reaf hiredes begymen.
Utitur mulier anabola, sed abutitur ipsabrycð wif healsmene ac bið scamlice brocen heo.
Conuenit apozima nec non placenta inualidisgedauenað broð eac swilce briw unhalum.
O cleronoma, maneas Codrus dissertus unaqueeala þu cleric wuna þu lareow gelæred þæt an.
Hau sis <luxorius> cum teneas yppos fiscone sy ðu to gal þonne þu healts hors on codde.

Careas nomine limphatici, ut sis Crissostomus; adsis apocrisarus, seruet os aforismos tibi; constes, basileus, abstemus antigraphusque; esto cosmographus, estoque catascopus tuiþola ðu naman gemindlyste þæt ðu sy gyldenmuðe æt sy ðu dihle þen gehealde muð dihle sprece þe gewuna þu kyninc sifre & inwritere beo þu middangeard todælend & beo þu emwlatend ðin.
Ne sis gimnus ab inlicitis, sisque biotticus autorNe sy ðu nacod fram unlyuendlicum & beo ðu woruldlic ealdor.

Celebres oroscopus acrizimum esque didascalus, habeasque amphiballum in thoro, et absit effebus; sed sit canterius abunde tibi, absit amasiusgelomlæc tid emwlatend þeorfne hlaf & beo þu larew & hafa þu ruhne hwitel on bedde & fram gewite se beardleasa ac sy hengest genihtsumiende þe gewite scanlufigende.
Careas fore cerritus atque perifrasticusþola þu wesan reðe & embspecende.
Niteat abbachus manui atque niteat theologus oriscine wexbred on hande & scine godcund spæc muðe.
Uideas ferre baccaulum fauste te cloaceforewarna þu beran bære gesæliglice þe pytte.
Hau sis prodigus, obliquus, monotalmus, subdolusne sy ðu tostencend gewed aneagede facenful.
Uites ludibrium, baratrum; sectare tropheum.forbuh þu þa bysmerlican helle fylig þu sige.
Stent procul amphitetra tibi necnon egilopia; nam generant scrupulum, uexantque pupillaswunian feorran wæuerstowa þe eac swylce eahwunda soðes cynað ancxsumnesse & gewriðuð seo.
Nitet analogiam scandito obrissis ore docentisscine healsmene beorhte golde muðe lærendes.
Declina birotum brauium accipito cliothedrumforbuh ðu twyhweolne sige onfoh þu fyldestol.
Habe culleum, scias diametra, nescias ergastulahafa þu picen fæt wite þu healfgemet nyte þu wræcstowa.
Apponas emistichium, cum sculpes disticaforesete ðu healffers ðænne þu writst twa fers.
Enoforo; suesce laxare lotiumon winfæte gewuna forlætan migeþan.
Dilige tu zenodochium, hodique zelotipialufa ðu þearfana hus & hata ðu hatunge.
Stringat hinc acitabula seu congia tuum domagewriðe heonenne ecedfæt oððe gemet þin hus.
Sit pomerium curti, sunt pomaria congrua malissy orcerdleh hirede synd orcerdas gedauenlice æpplum.
Fulgeat ostrum eclesiis, sit oletum longescine purpuren cyrcicum sy myx feor.
Statuant predia quala tibi; agitent flabra flagragesettan croftas wilian ðe astyrian windas gyrda.
Pota diamoron, ut fugiat gorgon eminusdrinc moroð þæt forfleo næddre feor.
Sperne tu olon platon, quatinus lustret odon te sinposiaforhige ðu eall fenn þanon onliht weg þe gebeorscipe.
Uigeas temeson, si non potes insons; nec absitque lucar, quo flagret lar nectar tibilufa þu healfscyldig gyf ðu ne miht scyldleas ne ne gewite wudufeoh þæt steme spichus swetnesse.
Esto memor tui gallonisbeo þu gemyndig þines medgyldan.
Timeto cieri ambro, neque sit tuus mulio strabo neque agason inermisondræd þu beon geciged gifre ne ne sy þin mulhyrde scyleage ne ne sy þin horshyrde wæpenleas.
Sit frequens hyrudo comitata, quo fuerit abbaso, ac disparet intercapedo citatim ualidossy gelomlic læce mid syðegod þær þær bið untrum hiwræden & tostence fæc hrædlice þa strangan.
Reminiscere tegat bule Christi mentem sibi tegat gausape mensam, si qua uirago penetret tuum domagemune þu ðæt oferwreo geþeaht mod him & þæt oferwreo sceat beod gyf hwilc fæmne infærð þine þæcene.
Comat entole te <te> regis baben proceresquegewlitegað bebod þe kyninges sweorbeah & ealdres.
Minime superet abdomen corpus, mage techenenig ne oferswið fætnes lichaman ma bebod.

Hau sis neoteritus uranii atque neophitus, sed priscus ab olim iugiter dogmatis ac fidei, ut iter comitentur hec quattuor immo in tuum euum: teche dei, ieron, archon palinodianquene sy þu niwe heofenlic & niwe on geleafan ac eald fram frymðe eallincg larum & geleafan eala ðer mid syðegodon þas fyower gyt ma on þinre ylde bebod godes halig ealdordom & geyðlæcan.
Uiuas ancisus, quin moriare cardiacuslifa þu ymsniden þeh þe ne swylte heortan cnysse.
Posce colimbum, si gestas ceruleas uestesgewilna þu wæschus gyf þu bere horige reaf.
Ducitur limbus anquina, ducitur nec non arsippio anquinabið gelæd scip mid rape bið gelæd eac swylc boga mid strence.
Equitatur canterius antelis postelisquebið geriden hengest mid forgyrdum & mid æfterræpum.

Sed patiaris et antropiam, ut acam congerat tua mens eius apodix ateruam sibi; anquirunt talia algemam mentis, uerum amendant aphatiam, edificant quoque largam anteceniamac þola þu & hlænnesse swa swa wynsumnesse gegæderige þin mod his gerefan ecelice him þearle secað swylce sargunge modes soðes afligað unþrowendlicnesse getimbriað eac swylce rumgyuelne nonmete.
Suffert agape nimis apta agapemforþyldegað lufe swyþe gecweme ælfremede geswinc.
Secteris acutis nisibus egidiam in girofylig þu mid scearpum higðum gat on ymhwyrfte.
Teneas agnatos, anheles quoque aregidiam uerbi, ne sis atratus in aslum hostisheald þu þa siblican gewilna þu eac swylce ren wordes ne sy þu bewependlic on herereaf feondum.
Ne angustent aulea sed alluat ethereus aprilax sceleris animam, ne fias apostatane ne genyrwian wahryfta ac geondgeote roderlic hæte gyltum saule þæt ðu ne sy wiðercora.
Geras ancile leua, agoniam fidei dextraber þu scyld mid wynstran gewin geleafan mid swryðran.
Amaneas auspicioutan wuna þu wiglunge.
Ampliet altum apogeum aliguam annonamgemænigfylde deop scræf.
Tollas armenum, addas archisteriumafyr þu wæuels geeacna þu mynster.
Colit architriclinus amicale amineum, atque honustat etiam autumnus apoforetabegæð beorscipes ealdor gecweme win & symð eac swylce hærfest æppelfæc.
Ast colat agamus antropus celibatum, et sic cernet Argiripam patriam beatosque ciues& begæð wifleas man clænnesse & swa he bewarað þa æþelican burh & þa eadigan ceastergewaran.

Haud est huic apoplexia cure, sed et astu nullos angustat, solet idem antiquare amartetes, aginat uenerem, portat anaboladiane is þysum þrowendlic deað begymen ac eac ænig ne genyrwð gewunað se sylua gecian þa earman he forflycð galscipe he byrð linenne wæuels.
Albent apoforeta huic alburnis pomis; comitantur illum amiciter cuncte uirtutesscinað æppelfata þysum hwitum æpplum mid syðegodon hine freondlice ealle mægna.

Non allidunt hunc sinistri affurcillando, et blatterat amineo si constiterint et referens eidem indignum, quoniam bittunt geniti bibiones e Bacho, haud bittit illo, quo bimetur quisquis honorene aslidað þysne deofla to beswicenne & wæfluð hwitan wine gyf gesettað & bringende for ðam þe forð gewitað þa acendan clystra wine ne ne gæð þider þær bið getwifeld swa hwilc wyrðment.
Fateor probum buteonem, qui bidentat burra arua; sed retinet hic et ingenuus similem genituramic andete godne geongan þe þe delf reade eorðan ac gehylt þes & æþelboren gelice æþelborennysse.

Et apparat buggeus uerum biliosus atque apparat bosor taphium sibi, sed biliosum; componit sic aratrum corpus anime uita, sed parat omnipotens leta astra, si est mens felix& getimbrað belysnad soðlice unrot & getimbrað gecweme byrgenne him ac unrote geset swa bewependlic lichama saule lif ac gegearwað ælmihtig bliðe tungla gyf is mod gesælig.
O tu, herilis miles, moneas cunctos hoc comitereala þu drihtenlica cempa mynga þu ealle þysum wel wyllendlice.

Cespitat preterea cum clandestinat quis culpam anthro atque communit clandestina in portu pectoris coalescens eius mentem comiter, si coagmentathryst forþan þonne bediglað hwa scyld on helle & geset dihla on hyðe breostes wexende his mod wel wyllendlice gyf gewrið.

Nam oluit illic clancule; non ualebit tamen constare ipsa diu clancula, tonante teste super per sacrata orasoþes bedihlað þær digellice ne framað swa ðeh hwaþere gewunian heo lange hean ælmihtigan gewitan wiðufan gynd þa gehalgedan gemæra.

O tutor, clientele maneas hic immo uelut heres dei, cum uideas pessumdare nefandum astum per secula quatinus ualeas scandere almos cliuos, quatinus ualeas clangere concinas laudes sistenti nomine modo tribus personis, soli tamen maiestate, nutu perhenni doxaqueeala þu scyldend hiwrædene wuna þu her gyt ma swa swa yrfweard þonne þu gesyhst forwurþan þa manfullan fræfelnesse geond worulde þæt þu mage astigan þa mæran cnollas & þæt þu mage swegan þa gesettan herunga wunigendum naman þæt an ðrym hadum anum swa þeh hwæþere mægðrymme andwealde & þa ecelican wuldor.
O tu clerice, poscas teneam quam pariter tecumeala þu cleric bide þu þæt ic healde þæt samod mid ðe.
